[test - Module 1: Introduction to Testing] Why is testing crucial in every field?

00:00:03.300 --> 00:00:35.510
[Defining Testing] Testing is a systematic process used to assess the functionality, quality, and reliability of products or processes. In software, for instance, testing ensures that applications perform as expected. Similarly, in education, testing gauges a learner's understanding. In what ways do you think testing impacts our daily lives? Think of the last time you encountered a bug in an app. Testing is the act of identifying and fixing these issues before they affect users.

00:00:35.910 --> 00:01:02.170
[Why Testing Matters] Testing holds paramount importance across industries, ensuring that products and services meet specified requirements. In healthcare, for example, medical devices undergo rigorous testing to save lives. In automobiles, testing enhances safety, preventing accidents. Can you imagine buying a car without crash tests? The goal of testing is to mitigate risks, safeguard users, and invest in quality.

00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:25.830
[Key Testing Principles] There are fundamental principles of testing that enhance its effectiveness. These include early testing to catch issues early, complete testing is an illusion, and defect clustering that recognizes most defects occur in a small number of modules. How might these principles change your perspective? Understanding these can shift your approach to quality and improvement.

00:01:26.230 --> 00:01:52.490
